dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Haslemere, solid and drift, sheet 301
dc_description_s: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 301 drift. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 51.166700. South Decimal Degree 50.9833. East Decimal Degree -0.4333. West Decimal Degree -0.8500. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of Great Britain. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights. Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Original geological survey on the one-inch scale by F. Drew et al. published on Old Series Sheet 8 (Solid) in 1862 and on Old Series Sheet 9 (Solid & Drift) in 1864. Drift deposits of Sheet 8 surveyed by W. Whitaker et al. published in 1887. Resurveyed on the six-inch scale by B. C. Worssam et al. in 1956-60." In lower right margin: "Based on the seventh one-inch map, parts of sheets 181 & 182 dated 1961, and 169 dated 1960.".
dc_publisher_s: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1969.
